Really if you think about it the guy isn&#39;t doing anything wrong per se..  He
makes claims and offers a disclaimer.  His biggest mistake is what feel is
the ethical decision to sell a Radio Shack radio without disclosing that
this could be done on their own.  But add in the software and the price then
doesn&#39;t seem so unrealistic.  But that IJMHO.  Of course his misinformed
info about Frank and his boxes is ridiculous but he might actually believe
this all to be true.   So in the end again I say Caveat emptor..  



  _____  

From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com [mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com] On Behalf Of
SnowfireL@...
Sent: Thursday, May 21, 2009 9:50 AM
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] Re: Ebay auction for sorta Frank&#39;s Box?








It&#39;s none of my business but, Frank will need to call ebay the number can be
found in the security section, and he will have to let them know they are
committing fraud, otherwise nothing will be done.  I saw these ads on ebay
too, but I thought, Frank may have been trying to earn some money for all
his hard work, nothing wrong with that either, that was before I joined
these groups. sf











In a message dated 5/21/2009 10:45:09 A.M. Eastern Daylight Time,
april@... writes:



Yeah-the seller, but you can&#39;t contact the bidders.



